<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Treasury Files</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Assistant</gloss> to the Secretary of the Treasury</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_WHD1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1944-09-25" notBefore="1944-09-13T20:00:00-04:00">undated</date>.<note n="1" xml:id="d566fn1">The date “9/25/44” which appears at the end of
                                    the memorandum is evidently the date of
                                typing.</note>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary’s
                                Files</hi></p>
                        <p>Dinner at the Citadel, Quebec, Wednesday, September 13, 1944, 8:00
                            p.m.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>However, the President came back to the German problem several times very
                            nicely and did not recede from his position. He reminded <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> that <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> at Teheran had said: “Are you
                            going to let Germany produce modern metal furniture? The manufacture of
                            metal furniture can be quickly turned into the manufacture of
                                armament.”<note n="2" xml:id="d566fn2">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_511">p. 511</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_WHD1">H. D. <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>